day 31 of crew matrix : add three numbers program 

IN C :
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int num1, num2, num3, sum;

    // Input three numbers
    printf("Enter three numbers: ");
    scanf("%d %d %d", &num1, &num2, &num3);

    // Calculate the sum
    sum = num1 + num2 + num3;

    // Display the result
    printf("The sum of %d, %d, and %d is: %d\n", num1, num2, num3, sum);

    return 0;
}

O/P : 
Enter three numbers: 5 10 15
The sum of 5, 10, and 15 is: 30

IN PYTHON : 
# Input three numbers
num1 = float(input("Enter the first number: "))
num2 = float(input("Enter the second number: "))
num3 = float(input("Enter the third number: "))

# Calculate the sum
sum = num1 + num2 + num3

# Display the result
print(f"The sum of {num1}, {num2}, and {num3} is: {sum}")

O/P :
Enter the first number: 5
Enter the second number: 10
Enter the third number: 15
The sum of 5.0, 10.0, and 15.0 is: 30.0
